original: Biber, Samuel (Sam), tandläkare, Göteborg, f. 10/5/04 i Tykosin, Ryssl., av grosshandl. Abr. Köpniwsky o. Ester Biber. G. 33 m. Vera Schatz. Barn: Ulla f. 34, Monica 37, Björn 44. — Stud :ex. i Växjö 23, med. kand. i Lund 28, tandl. 31. Vik. i Norberg 31-32, prakt. o. skoltandl. i Skene 32-42, skoltandl. i Gbg 42-43, egen prakt, där sed. 43.
translated: Biber, Samuel (Sam), dentist, Gothenburg, born May 10th, 1904 in Tykosin, Russia, son of merchant Abr. Köpniwsky and Ester Biber. Married in 1933 to Vera Schatz. Children: Ulla born in 1934, Monica in 1937, and Björn in 1944. He completed his studies in Växjö in 1923, obtained a medical degree in Lund in 1928, and became a dentist in 1931. He worked temporarily in Norberg from 1931 to 1932, then as a dental practitioner and school dentist in Skene from 1932 to 1942, and as a school dentist in Gothenburg from 1942 to 1943. He opened his own practice in Gothenburg in 1943 and continued to work there.
